Photo taken on Nov. 5, 2021 shows a mobile laboratory for nucleic acid tests in Harbin, northeast China's Heilongjiang Province. A mobile, inflatable laboratory for conducting COVID-19 tests was officially put into use on Nov. 1 at a sports center in Harbin. The laboratory can cope with swab samples from 1.75 million people for nucleic acid tests per day. (Xinhua/Wang Jianwei)  